description: From New Latin abelmoschus, from Arabic حَبّ الْمِسْك‎ (ḥabb al-misk, “pills of musk”).

entries.meaning: The edible and aromatic seed pods (properly, capsules) of the Abelmoschus moschatus.
examples: Egyptian Ketmia, with a perfumed or Musk-Seed..., called Abelmosch of Morison.

entries.meaning: The tropical evergreen shrub Abelmoschus moschatus itself.
examples: Abelmosk, Abelmosch, or Abelmusk, the Syrian mallow, or musk okro, a species of hibiscus (H. abelmoschus).

entries.meaning: (uncommon, usually in the plural) Other members of the genus Abelmoschus, such as okra.
